Changes from version 2.0

New Features:

Erik Johnson's ARROW function has been incorporated into
MatDraw.  There is now an Arrow submenu in the Draw Menu
which allows the user to convert regular lines to arrows
and vice-versa.  There is also a dialog box accessible 
through the Arrow Tips menu item in the Arrow submenu which
allows control of the size and shape of the arrows.  To 
take advantage of the 3D arrows allowed by Erik's function,
3D drawing and resizing of lines is now possible in MatDraw.
Specification of coordinates is done in the same way as in
the 3D zoom function which was available in MatDraw 2.0. 
Note that due to quirks in MATLAB's processing of mouse clicks,
it may sometimes be difficult to select a specific line in a
3D plot.  This occurs when the object is "behind" a surface object.
For details, see the Release Notes for MATLAB 4.2.  

In the Workspace Menu an item called "Add to Path" has been
added.  This brings up a standard "open" dialog box; to add
a directory to your MATLABPATH simply use the dialog box to
select a file in the relevant directory.

Changes:

The Page Title item in the Figure Menu has been subsumed into
the Labels dialog box.

Bug Fixes:

A couple of capitalization mistakes have been found and corrected.

The order in which properties were assigned in creation of some
uicontrols in certain dialog boxes was such that they came out 
looking wrong on some platforms, most notably the SGI.  This has
been fixed.

Text rotation did not work properly.  It has been fixed.

When creating a text object, clicking outside of the edit uicontrol
created a new edit uicontrol and rendered the former one unusable.
Now, when you click outside of an edit uicontrol whatever was in
the last one is registered and it is dismissed.




